  "steps": [
    {
      "order": 1,
      "instruction": "Pickle first - Put the boiling water, salt and sugar in a bowl. Mix to to dissolve, then add vinegar. Submerge vegetables and leave for 2 hours. Drain then use per recipe (or store in fridge submerged in liquid)."
    },
    {
      "order": 2,
      "instruction": "Peanut sauce - Mix the peanut sauce ingredients and set aside for the flavours to meld while you prepare the platter. Start with 1 tbsp lime juice and add more if you want tarter."
    },
    {
      "order": 3,
      "instruction": "Prawns (shrimp) - Cut the prawns in half horizontally and remove the vein."
    },
    {
      "order": 4,
      "instruction": "Noodles - Soak the noodles in boiling water per packet directions. Rinse under cold water (to prevent stickiness) then drain very well."
    },
    {
      "order": 5,
      "instruction": "Lay it all out - Pile everything onto a giant platter or put things in little bowls, then let everybody help themselves!"
    },
    {
      "order": 6,
      "instruction": "Assemble - Here&#39;s my order: lettuce leaf, noodles first, then veg* (carrots, bean sprouts etc), prawns, stuff herbs down the side, drizzle with sauce, sprinkle with peanuts and chilli. Bundle and bite!"
    }
  ]
